<p>The <code>cut</code> function removes all occurrences of a substring.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'hello-world' | cut('-'){close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo 'hello-world' | cut('-')}</b></p>

<h2>Remove Prefix</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'prefix_name' | cut('prefix_'){close}</pre>
<p>Without prefix: <b>{echo 'prefix_name' | cut('prefix_')}</b></p>

<h2>Remove Characters</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'a.b.c.d' | cut('.'){close}</pre>
<p>No dots: <b>{echo 'a.b.c.d' | cut('.')}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'Mr. John Smith' | cut('Mr. ') | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Name only: <b>{echo 'Mr. John Smith' | cut('Mr. ') | upper}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo '123-456-7890' | cut('-') | left(6){close}</pre>
<p>First 6 digits: <b>{echo '123-456-7890' | cut('-') | left(6)}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'test_file_name.txt' | cut('_') | beforeLast('.'){close}</pre>
<p>Clean name: <b>{echo 'test_file_name.txt' | cut('_') | beforeLast('.')}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The <code>cut</code> function is shorthand for <code>replace(text, '')</code>.</p>
